cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper deals with decision making under uncertainty in voting scenarios, which is a key topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a framework for handling uncertainty without detailed probabilistic information, which involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses this framework to justify various known voting heuristics, which is related to the field of mechanism design (cs.MA).
